# Stationarity in Oct gold etf prices
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller
from numpy import log
result = adfuller(Oct_ETF_prices.values)
print('ADF Statistic: %f' % result[0])
print('p-value: %f' % result[1]) # if p-val > critical ci then we go ahead with differencing

ADF Statistic: -1.637974
p-value: 0.463320

In [40]:
# finding the right difference term for Oct-gold prices

from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf
plt.rcParams.update({'figure.figsize':(9,7), 'figure.dpi':120})


# Original Series
fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 2, sharex=True)
axes[0, 0].plot(Oct_ETF_prices.values); axes[0, 0].set_title('Original Series')
plot_acf(Oct_ETF_prices.values, ax=axes[0, 1])

# 1st Differencing
axes[1, 0].plot(np.diff(Oct_ETF_prices.values)); axes[1, 0].set_title('1st Order Differencing')
plot_acf(np.diff(Oct_ETF_prices.values), ax=axes[1, 1])

# 2nd Differencing
axes[2, 0].plot(np.diff(np.diff(Oct_ETF_prices.values))); axes[2, 0].set_title('2nd Order Differencing')
plot_acf((np.diff(np.diff(Oct_ETF_prices.values))), ax=axes[2, 1])

plt.show()

# finding the right difference term in Nov gold ETF prices

from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
plt.rcParams.update({'figure.figsize':(9,7), 'figure.dpi':120})


# Original Series
fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 2, sharex=True)
axes[0, 0].plot(Nov_ETF_prices.values); axes[0, 0].set_title('Original Series')
plot_acf(Nov_ETF_prices.values, ax=axes[0, 1])

# 1st Differencing
axes[1, 0].plot(np.diff(Nov_ETF_prices.values)); axes[1, 0].set_title('1st Order Differencing')
plot_acf(np.diff(Nov_ETF_prices.values), ax=axes[1, 1])

# 2nd Differencing
axes[2, 0].plot(np.diff(np.diff(Nov_ETF_prices.values))); axes[2, 0].set_title('2nd Order Differencing')
plot_acf((np.diff(np.diff(Nov_ETF_prices.values))), ax=axes[2, 1])

plt.show()

# finding the best model for Oct-ETF gold prices
import pmdarima as pm

model = pm.auto_arima(Oct_ETF_prices.values, start_p=0, start_q=0,
                      test='adf',       # use adftest to find optimal 'd'
                      max_p=3, max_q=3, # maximum p and q
                      m=1,              # frequency of series
                      d=None,           # let model determine 'd'
                      seasonal=False,   # No Seasonality
                      start_P=0, 
                      D=0, 
                      trace=True,
                      error_action='ignore',  
                      suppress_warnings=True, 
                      stepwise=True)

print(model.summary())
